UID:xUJ4ZM7_HjIIPsIn2Izms
SUMMARY:2026 Spring Fundraiser with Lynda Mapes
DTSTAMP:20260301T153241Z
DTSTART:20260312T003000Z
DESCRIPTION:"The Trees are Speaking" with author Lynda Mapes The power of p
	ersistence. A celebration of renewal.  We're excited to announce that Lynd
	a Mapes will headline the Forterra Spring Fundraiser. This vibrant celebra
	tion will be Wednesday\, March 11\, 2026\, at Fremont Foundry in Seattle-o
	ur largest annual fundraiser supporting Forterra's core mission. Friends o
	ld and new will connect over drinks\, a delicious dinnerand engaging conve
	rsation. Registration opens in January 2026. About Lynda Mapes: Lynda V. M
	apes specializes in coverage of the environment and Indigenous cultures an
	d governments. Over the course of her 27-year career as a reporter at The 
	Seattle Times she earned numerous awards\, including twice winning the int
	ernational 2019 and 2012 Kavli gold award for science journalism from the 
	American Association for the Advancement of Science\, the world's largest 
	professional science association. She and a team of journalists at the Sea
	ttle Times were finalists for the 2025 Pulitzer Prize for local reporting.
	 She has written seven books\, including most recently The Trees are Speak
	ing\, Dispatches from the Salmon Forests just published by the University 
	of Washington Press. She is the winner of the 2021 National Outdoor Book A
	ward\, and 2021 Washington State Book Award for non-fiction. She is an ass
	ociate of the Harvard Forest\, and lives in Seattle. Learn more about Lynd
	a Mapes.  Event date 5:30 p.m. to 8 p.m.\, Wednesday\, March 11\, 2026 Loc
	ation Fremont Foundry 154 N 35th St Seattle\, WA 98103 Registration Opens 
	in January 2026.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/2026-spr
	ing-fundraiser-with-lynda-mapes/17654947/2026-03-11T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - 
	Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/2026-spring-fundraiser-wi
